cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a methodology to detect the partial pose of a human occupying the manipulator work-space using on-robot sensors. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The proposed methodology uses a highly sparse 3-D point cloud input to estimate the partial pose of the human. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed methodology leverages an artificial neural network to perform the detection. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents a particle filter based approach to the tracking problem when the input data is unreliable. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper presents simulation results and analysis, which may involve graphics and visualization.
